Fairly easy when they are throwing molotov @#%$ and chanting "Yankee go home". There had been a recent (at the time, not recent to today) incident where some US servicemen had been involved in an accident of some sort, and it had resulted in a few Koreans dying in a fire. Perhaps their blood was simply up over that (like the US soldier in Japan accused of raping a japanese woman several years back), but the faces in that crowd were more than just hormone infused college students looking to duck final exams by protesting. You have personal experience that I do not.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">A carrier group is one of the most powerful extentions of military might known to man, but they're expensive and they require constant upgrading/refitting. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
