Not quite true.  A nuke is actually very, very simple to build unless you just <span style="font-style: italic">want</span> to make it complex, and can still be very effective.  All it really takes is a disk of lithium, a disk of polonium, the proper type of uranium, a steel rod and a small amount of plastic explosive.  Getting ahold of those is fairly difficult for your average civilian, but for a government, and even most terrorist groups, it's not that hard.
