Well, there have been lengthy scholarly volumnes written by people far more knowledgeable than you or I about what we *could* have done in Vietnam that might have changed the outcome. I have somewhere buried in a box a book I inherited written by a General during the time, it's 700ish pages. I've skimmed through parts of it, and a portion talks about the initial stages of the Hearts&Minds campaign, and how effective that was until the CIA got involved and changed it. Maybe if that had come out differently it would have altered the whole conflict. Who knows.
