<br />
For folks interested in the targeting doctrine look up Operation Rolling Thunder.  Targets were given priority.  The highest strategic priority was the "Alpha" list.  However, this list was avoided.  Industrial targets were on the "Alpha" list.  This list wasn't hit until late and not very much.  Washinton avoided it so as not to @#%$ off the civilian population (or so they thought).  Ports were also avoided (also on the "Alpha" list) so as not to @#%$ of the USSR.  Basically, politics got in the way of military decisions.<span class="gensmall"></span>


